Hi
You'll find logic exercise sheets 6 and 7 on the web now, at the 
usual place 
http://www.doc.ic.ac.uk/~imh/teaching/140_logic/logic.html.  The 
solutions to sheet 6 will be out on Friday.

Regarding part c of Q6 on sheet 6: there seem to
be some misunderstanding to what the question is asking for. Maybe 
the question could be made clearer by rephrasing as:



(c):
(i) It is not possible to find structures M and N such that:
--- M makes the first sentence in (a) true and the second sentence in 
(a) false,
--- N makes the first sentence in (a) false and the second sentence 
in (a) true.
Why?

(ii) Repeat part c(i) using the sentences in (b) instead of those in (a).



Any kind of clear and convincing explanation would be useful as an 
answer.  The question is not asking for a formal proof.


Ian H
